## ğŸ§® PART 2 â€” Computed Property Exercises

### **Exercise C1 â€” Temperature Range**
Create a struct:
```swift
struct DayTemperature {
    var low: Int
    var high: Int
    var range: String { "\(low)â€“\(high)Âº" }
}
```

Display `range` inside a Text view.

---

### **Exercise C2 â€” Progress Model**
```swift
struct ProgressInfo {
    var completed: Int
    var total: Int
    var fraction: Double { Double(completed) / Double(total) }
    var label: String { "\(completed) of \(total)" }
}
```

Render these in a SwiftUI view.

---

### **Exercise C3 â€” Category Property**
```swift
struct Score {
    var value: Int
    var category: String {
        switch value {
        case ..<50: "Low"
        case 50..<75: "Medium"
        default: "High"
        }
    }
}
```

Use this to change the displayed text color.

